programme.title: Defense Delivers Closing Arguments
programme.desc: During the final remarks to the jury, the State expounded on their murder timeline. This timeline ended in the poisoning death of Rosemarie Essa and her husband, Yazeed, fleeing the country on the run from the law.

programme.title: Leave Emotion Out
programme.desc: Yazeed Essa's lawyer was in the middle of their closing arguments.

programme.title: Lacking Direct Evidence
programme.desc: The long closing arguments by the Defense continued. Defense attorney Steven Bradley continued to stress the lack of physical evidence the state needed to link Yazeed to his wife, Rosemarie's death.

programme.title: The Long Final Remarks To Jurors
programme.desc: Jurors listened to Yazeed Essa's attorney during closing arguments trying to implicate one of his mistresses as the possible killer in Rosemarie's death.

programme.title: Closing Rebuttal
programme.desc: Yazeed Essa's attorney wrapped up his long closing arguments to jurors in his murder trial.

programme.title: The Incomplete Marriage
programme.desc: In the State's closing arguments, Steven Dever, the lead prosecutor, explained why Yazeed all of abandoned his two kids to flee the U.S. as police began looking at him as a murder suspect.

programme.title: The Fugitive Doctor's Fate
programme.desc: Just before jury deliberations, the defense called for a mistrial over statements prosecutors made to the jury. The judge denied that motion. Yazeed Essa faced life in prison if convicted in the poisoning death of his wife, Rosemarie.

programme.title: An Emotional Sentencing
programme.desc: The sentencing phase of Yazeed Essa began with emotional victim-impacted statements. After four days of jury deliberations, he was convicted for intentionally poisoning his wife to death.

programme.desc: The verdict comes down.
